Cucumbers contain magnesium, potassium, and vitamin K. These 3 nutrients are vital for the proper functioning of the cardiovascular system. Cucumber is made up of 96% water. The water can help keep you hydrated. Plus, the fiber boost they give you helps your gut system stay healthy and avoid constipation. Ingredients Preparation Step 1 In a large bowl, sprinkle the cucumbers with salt. Step 2 Allow the cucumbers to sit with the salt so that the juices drain. Step 3 In a pan, over medium heat, saute the red onions with the remaining ingredients. Step 4 Toss to combine the onions with the cucumbers and put in the refrigerator for an hour before serving. Enjoy with your favourite chicken or fish.